== Sagat Patch ==
* Sagat released
<br>

== '''Character Changes''' ==

=== '''A.K.I.''' ===
* Venomous Fang (2PP~P) shifted the projectile invincible hurtbox downward immediately after startup (to ensure it's possible to attack through a Low Tiger Shot)
<br>

=== '''Akuma''' ===
* Adamant Flame Follow-up (214P~6P) fixed an issue where the attack could not be performed while a projectile was on the screen
* {{clr|OD|Demon Gou Rasen}} ({{clr|OD|236KK}}~{{clr|OD|j.214K}}) fixed an issue where the attack could not be performed while a projectile was on the screen
* {{clr|SA|SA1}} / {{clr|SA|Air SA1}} changed the amount of Drive Gauge gained on Perfect Parry is the same as other Super Arts (20000)
<br>

=== '''Blanka''' ===
* Backstep Rolling Attack (63214K/{{clr|OD|KK}}) fixed an issue where holding forward/back would steer Blanka a different distance depending on whether he was facing left or right
<br>

=== '''Cammy''' ===
* Spiral Arrow (236K/{{clr|OD|KK}}) hurtbox expanded upward at the start and during later active frames (to ensure it cannot easily pass under High Tiger Shot)
** {{clr|L|236LK}}: frames 1-2, 14-21
** {{clr|M|236MK}}: frames 1-2, 14-23
** {{clr|H|236HK}}: frames 1-5, 23-32
** {{clr|OD|236KK}}: frames 1-4, 19-29
* {{clr|SA|SA1}} ({{clr|SA|236236K}}) upper hurtbox on frames 1-5 that is vulnerable to projectiles expanded upward
** This ensures that the early startup frames cannot duck under a High Tiger Shot
<br>

=== '''Chun-Li''' ===
* {{clr|SA|Critical Art}} ({{clr|SA|214214K}}) fixed an issue where the opponent would gain less Drive Gauge when parrying the attack compared to other Super Arts
<br>

=== '''Dhalsim''' ===
* {{clr|L|2LK}} projectile invincible hurtbox shifted downward (to ensure it's possible to slide under Low Tiger Shot with good timing)
<br>

=== '''Ed''' ===
* {{clr|L|LP Psycho Uppercut}} ({{clr|L|623LP}}) fixed an issue where Ed could cancel the final 4 recovery frames into another action on whiff
<br>

=== '''E. Honda''' ===
* Neko Damashi (22P) fixed an issue where buffering a {{clr|SA|SA3/CA}} input would not work
<br>

=== '''Elena''' ===
* {{clr|H|Round Arch}} ({{clr|H|4HK}}) fixed an issue where Elena would slide forward when performed out of {{clr|DR|Drive Rush}} when not inputting a direction
* {{clr|SA|Critical Art}} ({{clr|SA|214214K}}) fixed an issue where the damage value was increased by 1000 when landing a K.O. against the opponent
<br>

=== '''Kimberly''' ===
* {{clr|OD|OD Sprint}} ({{clr|OD|236KK}}) Modern Controls ({{clr|DR|A[6S]}}) fixed an issue where Down+Forward / Down+Back + Attack would perform Neck Hunter / Emergency Stop instead of Shadow Slide
<br>

=== '''Luke''' ===
* {{clr|OD|OD Avenger}} ({{clr|OD|236KK}}) armored head hurtbox shifted downward (to prevent interference with High Tiger Shot)
<br>

=== '''M. Bison''' ===
* {{clr|DR|Drive Impact}} fixed an issue where the armor could absorb 3 or more hits depending on which part of the body they interacted with
<br>

=== '''Manon''' ===
* {{clr|H|Temps Lié}} ({{clr|H|5HP}}~{{clr|H|HP}}) fixed an issue where Manon could Parry on the final recovery frame on block
<br>

=== '''Marisa''' ===
* {{clr|M|2MP}} upper hurtboxes made projectile invincible (to prevent interference with High Tiger Shot)
* {{clr|M|2MK}} upper hurtboxes made projectile invincible (to prevent interference with High Tiger Shot)
* {{clr|H|2HK}} upper hurtboxes made projectile invincible (to prevent interference with High Tiger Shot)
<br>

=== '''Rashid''' ===
<section begin=2.00 Rashid />
* {{clr|H|2HP}} upper hurtboxes made projectile invincible (to prevent interference with High Tiger Shot)
** ''Note: the official patch notes incorrectly attributed this change to {{clr|H|2HK}}''
<br>
<section end=2.00 Rashid />

=== '''Terry''' ===
* {{clr|OD|214}}{{clr|L|LP}}{{clr|H|HP}} input changed from {{clr|OD|OD Burning Knuckle}} to {{clr|OD|OD Quick Burn}}
* {{clr|SA|SA3/CA}} ({{clr|SA|236236P}}) fixed an issue where the opponent would gain less Drive Gauge compared to other Super Arts on parry or Perfect Parry
<br>

=== '''Zangief''' ===
* Parry hurtbox from frame 3 onward expanded forward
** This is to match the hurtbox expansion Zangief received in the June 2025 update
* {{clr|M|2MP}} upper hurtboxes made projectile invincible (to prevent interference with High Tiger Shot)
* Tundra Storm ({{clr|H|22HK}}) counter hitbox expanded upward (allowing it to work against Sagat's {{clr|H|5HK}}/{{clr|H|6HK}})
* Double Lariat (Modern Controls: {{clr|M|M}}+{{clr|H|H}}) reverted the change that allowed {{clr|L|L}}+{{clr|M|M}}+{{clr|H|H}} to perform Double Lariat instead of Throw while in Burnout
** This is due to a bug that caused the move to come out in unintended situations, and is planned to be reimplemented.  
<br>